OL,6,FBBC Presentation has always allowed a
OL,7,Fdegree of slippage either way which
OL,8,Fcommercial broadcasters can't
OL,9,Faccommodate.
OL,11,FFor instance, the main news
OL,12,Fprogrammes nearly always come out a
OL,13,Ffew seconds under or over.
OL,15,FBut it has always been clearly
OL,16,Funderstood that Presentation can
OL,17,Fsimply haul an overrunning programme
OL,18,Foff the air if necessary.
